    <p>SAR­RAN COR­REZE</p>
    <p>(France) • Af­ter two near misses, Marc Hirschi grabbed a Tour de France win yes­ter­day at the end of the long­est stage this year.</p>
    <p>The Swiss was too strong for a dis­or­gan­ised pur­su­ing group in the run-in on a rolling 218km Stage 12 ride from Chau­vi­gny to Sar­ran.</p>
    <p>Slove­nian Pri­moz Roglic fin­ished in the main pack and kept hold of the yel­low jer­sey with a 21-sec­ond lead over de­fend­ing cham­pion Egan Ber­nal.</p>


